sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(contact_id) as contact_count
FROM user_contacts
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "gardeners" refers to active users who are not in the 'admin' role;
- "watering cans" is a metaphor for user email addresses;
- "soil" symbolizes the companies they work for;
- "cherished seedlings" represent contacts marked as favorites.
